> You asked, we listened: This isn't the HelloFresh you remember. Bigger menu. Upgraded recipes. Increased portion sizes. More variety. The best way to cook dinner just got BETTER.

> One of our favorite cheffy tricks for taking meatballs from ordinary to extraordinary? Just add a flavorful glaze! Here, we blend scallions and ginger into ground beef, then form into meatballs and roast until tender. While they're still hot from the oven, we toss them in a blend of soy glaze and chili sauce for spicy, sweet, and savory notes. They're served over a stir-fry of tender bell pepper, carrots, green beans, and citrusy ponzu sauce, then sprinkled with sesame seeds for nutty crunch.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced, whites and greens separated), separating whites from greens; mince whites. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and sliced into strips) into strips.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, scallion whites, half the ginger, half the @soy sauce{2%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), @salt{1/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}.

Form mixture into 10-12 (20-24 for 4) 1 1⁄2-inch meatballs. Spread out on a #baking sheet{}.

Bake on top rack until meatballs are browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

== Stir-Fry Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green beans and cook until slightly softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in bell pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender, ~{4-5%minutes} more.

Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce}; cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters}, half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving), remaining ginger, and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to pan with veggies. Cook, stirring, until ginger is fragrant and butter has melted, ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

Remove pan from heat; keep covered until ready to serve.

== Soy-Glaze and Assembly ==

In a second #large microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon} with @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}; microwave until just warmed through, ~{30%seconds}.

Once meatballs are fully cooked, carefully add to bowl and toss with sauce to coat.

Divide veggie stir-fry between plates or shallow bowls; top with meatballs and any remaining sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens and remaining sesame seeds. Serve.